  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Edit: Auto-Update Motions</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2"><text styleclass="Heading2" translate="true">Auto-Update Motion</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="AStandard" rowcount="2" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:24px; height:19px; background-color:#ccffcc;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:right;"><image src="Edittoolbar-Rebuiild.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="height:19px;">
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="text-decoration:none;" translate="true">Auto-Update </text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">is active when the </text><text styleclass="T_Menu 10p" translate="true">Edit toolbar &gt; Auto-Update icon </text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">is &apos;colourized&apos;.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">If you edit the motion, the model in </text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true"> will update.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">We recommend that Auto-Update is active when:</text></para>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">the model is simple and you want to update quickly</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" translate="true">you want to scrutinize fine changes near the end of the design optimisation.</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:24px; background-color:#ccffcc;">
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-align:right;"><image src="Edittoolbar-Rebuiild-off.png" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">Auto-Update is not active</text><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">The </text><text styleclass="T_Menu 10p" translate="true">Edit toolbar &gt; Auto-Update </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">is Toggled Out.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-weight:bold; font-style:italic;" translate="true">If you edit a motion, the model in MechDesigner</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true"> does not update.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="text-decoration:underline;" translate="true">It is much faster to edit the motions</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo" translate="true">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#ff6600;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Body Text" translate="true">We recommend that Auto-Update is not active when you want to make many changes to a motion, and do not want to review each change.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
